00:18.471 --> 00:20.491
I thought he was supposed
to have a breakfast date, right?

00:20.640 --> 00:22.326
I mean, they told me
that last night.

00:22.475 --> 00:24.495
Breakfast?
Is that on the sched?

00:24.643 --> 00:25.830
It isn't,
but the lieutenant told me

00:25.977 --> 00:27.498
that he'd be doing
breakfast with someone

00:27.646 --> 00:28.999
down at the harbor.

00:29.146 --> 00:30.167
I mean, if he ain't,

00:30.314 --> 00:32.769
I could go get this gassed up
at the Fallsway.

00:32.917 --> 00:35.271
I hate this detail, man.

00:35.419 --> 00:38.474
It's off duty.
Lotsa perks.

00:38.621 --> 00:43.011
All this stand around
and wait, you know?

00:43.159 --> 00:45.013
Hoskins says
I do the one year,

00:45.161 --> 00:46.848
and I'll make sergeant
on the next list.

00:46.995 --> 00:49.017
Yeah. They told me,
careerwise,

00:49.164 --> 00:50.518
you can't do better
than drive the mayor.

00:50.666 --> 00:52.353
Shit, if you could
make rank the right way,

00:52.501 --> 00:54.765
I'll still be working
Western drugs.

01:05.946 --> 01:06.966
All right, fuck this,

01:07.113 --> 01:08.600
I'm gonna go look
for the lieutenant.

01:08.748 --> 01:09.635
Anyone comes looking,

01:09.783 --> 01:12.445
I'm back up
on the second floor.

01:19.291 --> 01:20.311
Sir?

01:20.459 --> 01:21.479
I understood
that the mayor

01:21.626 --> 01:24.147
might be going to, uh,
breakfast at the harbor?

01:24.295 --> 01:25.649
With Kweisi.

01:25.797 --> 01:27.984
But, um, that's up
in the air, I thought.

01:28.132 --> 01:31.465
Would you happen to know
where Lieutenant Hoskins is?

01:54.722 --> 01:56.315
Sir?

02:04.264 --> 02:05.754
Lieutenant?

02:07.934 --> 02:09.264
Umm...

04:19.916 --> 04:22.438
You don't look happy,
Detective.

04:22.586 --> 04:26.108
We're about
to raise some hell.

04:26.255 --> 04:29.111
Maybe too much hell.

04:29.258 --> 04:32.480
A state senator,
two councilmen,

04:32.628 --> 04:34.382
the City Development Agency,

04:34.530 --> 04:35.917
all those developers...

04:36.065 --> 04:37.117
Princes of the city.

04:37.266 --> 04:39.119
Lester, tell me
the thought hasn't

04:39.267 --> 04:40.621
crossed your mind
that some kinda shit

04:40.769 --> 04:42.556
could blow
back on us, man.

04:42.704 --> 04:44.290
Do you know what
Theodore Roosevelt said

04:44.439 --> 04:46.960
about hunting grizzly bears?

04:47.107 --> 04:50.029
The thrill is in overcoming
your own fear.

04:50.177 --> 04:52.371
What was the thrill
for the bear?

04:55.616 --> 04:57.136
I should've run every one
of these subpoenas

04:57.283 --> 04:58.169
by my front office.

04:58.317 --> 04:59.638
That's not procedure.

04:59.786 --> 05:02.539
Fuck procedure, Lester.

05:02.688 --> 05:04.074
My boss is running
two points behind

05:04.222 --> 05:06.377
in the polls with
the mayor's support.

05:06.525 --> 05:07.411
How do you think
he's gonna do

05:07.559 --> 05:08.579
if he pisses off Royce

05:08.727 --> 05:10.080
and starts dropping off
incumbent tickets?

05:10.227 --> 05:12.683
Why do you care?

05:12.830 --> 05:15.752
If Demper thinks
I fucked him and he wins,

05:15.900 --> 05:19.087
I will be at Central Booking
covering bail reviews.

05:19.236 --> 05:20.423
If he loses to Bond,

05:20.570 --> 05:22.090
a new front office comes
in and maybe they bounce

05:22.238 --> 05:23.792
the white girl
back to a trial team

05:23.940 --> 05:25.927
and give the Narcotics Division
to one of their own.

05:26.074 --> 05:28.429
It's Baltimore, Lester.

05:28.578 --> 05:30.598
We're missing
a couple of subpoenas.

05:30.746 --> 05:32.236
We are?

05:33.414 --> 05:37.104
Clay Davis
and Andy Krawczyk.

05:37.251 --> 05:39.105
I'm holding those
till October.

05:39.253 --> 05:40.607
Oh, the hell you are.

05:40.755 --> 05:41.741
Lester...

05:41.888 --> 05:44.109
we drop subpoenas
on either of those guys

05:44.258 --> 05:45.944
three weeks
before the primary,

05:46.093 --> 05:47.614
and all hell breaks loose.

05:47.761 --> 05:49.381
That's what I'm sayin'!

05:49.529 --> 05:52.284
Clay Davis is Royce's
deputy campaign chairman,

05:52.432 --> 05:55.119
and the number-two man at
the City Legislative Caucus.

05:55.267 --> 05:57.388
And Krawczyk is his
number-one fundraiser!

05:57.536 --> 05:59.557
You're giving me resumes
and job titles.

05:59.704 --> 06:01.459
I'm just following the money.

06:01.607 --> 06:04.728
And we will follow it...
after the polls close.

06:04.876 --> 06:06.897
We can drop a second batch
of subpoenas.

06:07.045 --> 06:09.865
There is no reason to do
this now and risk--

06:10.014 --> 06:12.401
A year ago, if we had gone
after these records,

06:12.550 --> 06:14.737
City Hall would've
stomped on this unit

06:14.885 --> 06:16.405
and the subpoenas.

06:16.553 --> 06:19.908
And a month from now,
after Royce is reelected,

06:20.057 --> 06:22.377
they'll do us
the same way.

06:22.525 --> 06:26.647
But right now,
with the primary coming,

06:26.796 --> 06:28.415
they gotta worry
about how they look,

06:28.563 --> 06:30.360
how they behave.

06:31.566 --> 06:35.229
Right now, they gotta
worry about scandal.

06:38.405 --> 06:40.259
You told me you wanted
to do this a year ago,

06:40.407 --> 06:43.069
but fresh cases
got in the way.

06:46.246 --> 06:48.646
You told me that.

06:50.016 --> 06:52.771
Oh.

06:52.918 --> 06:55.272
Very clever, Lester.

06:55.420 --> 06:57.842
You got it all figured, huh?

06:57.990 --> 07:00.778
Me?

07:00.925 --> 07:03.689
I'm just the police.

07:06.197 --> 07:08.885
I saw the teachers' union
finally endorsed Royce.

07:09.032 --> 07:11.227
You knew
they were gonna.

07:17.039 --> 07:18.894
What time's
your first appearance?

07:19.041 --> 07:20.062
Today?

07:20.209 --> 07:22.897
I meet up with you guys
at the SoWeBo forum.

07:23.045 --> 07:25.233
And tonight, it's me
and the kids next to Tommy

07:25.380 --> 07:28.042
at the Roland Park fundraiser.

07:34.555 --> 07:37.076
Better speed things along.

07:37.225 --> 07:40.057
A kick in the ass
sometimes helps.

07:41.395 --> 07:45.917
- B-5?
- No, Daddy, D-5.

07:46.065 --> 07:47.752
You sure
you didn't say B-5?

07:47.900 --> 07:50.588
D-5.
What did I hit?

07:50.736 --> 07:52.225
Submarine.

07:54.073 --> 07:56.593
Umm...

07:56.741 --> 07:58.595
E-6.

07:58.743 --> 08:00.074
Miss.

08:03.347 --> 08:04.534
Just gimme 10 minutes.

08:04.683 --> 08:05.868
You seen your
schedule today?

08:06.016 --> 08:07.203
You ain't got
10 minutes.

08:07.351 --> 08:09.372
Norman, I got
this pretty girl's

08:09.519 --> 08:11.206
aircraft carrier boxed in.

08:11.354 --> 08:15.210
- D-4.
- Ow! Hit.

08:15.358 --> 08:16.878
Tommy,
for Christ's sakes.

08:17.025 --> 08:19.147
Is there any way
that I can win?

08:19.294 --> 08:21.549
With the numbers what they are,
is there any way at all?

08:21.697 --> 08:24.051
Right, so if it's just a matter
of playing out the string,

08:24.198 --> 08:25.219
then that's what
I'm gonna do.

08:25.366 --> 08:26.719
That game's pretty much
over, Norman.

08:26.868 --> 08:29.756
But this game--
this game right here--

08:29.904 --> 08:32.530
this one could still
go either way.

08:34.374 --> 08:35.395
H-11,
sweetheart.

08:35.542 --> 08:37.135
Miss. D-3.

09:27.355 --> 09:30.042
So I guess y'all getting
what y'all need?

09:30.190 --> 09:32.711
- Brianna keepin' y'all close?
- She come up with it.

09:32.860 --> 09:35.214
Money comin' through
every month like she say.

09:35.361 --> 09:37.782
A'ight, 'cause I'm standin'
tall up in here.

09:37.930 --> 09:39.584
They don't need
to worry about me

09:39.732 --> 09:41.218
an' I ain't need
to worry about them.

09:41.367 --> 09:44.200
- You a soldier, Bey.
- You know it.

09:45.871 --> 09:48.492
Everything all right
with my fishes?

09:48.640 --> 09:50.194
You'd tell me if
it wasn't, right?

09:50.341 --> 09:53.229
The fish be fine.
I mean, they fish, right?

09:53.378 --> 09:55.064
How I know how they
feelin' about shit?

09:55.212 --> 09:57.066
- De'londa...
- They fine, Bey.

09:57.214 --> 09:58.734
Ask Namond.

09:58.883 --> 10:00.569
Cleaned the tank an' all,
like you say.

10:00.718 --> 10:03.572
- Cleaned the filter, too.
- A'ight, a'ight.

10:03.720 --> 10:04.706
Check you out, though.

10:04.854 --> 10:07.074
Getting some fuzz
up there, huh?

10:07.223 --> 10:09.144
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah, whatever.

10:09.291 --> 10:10.778
I know when I was
a little kid, boy,

10:10.927 --> 10:12.647
I couldn't wait till
I started shaving.

10:12.795 --> 10:14.315
One of the old heads
on the corner say,

10:14.463 --> 10:17.084
"Hey, little man,
you wanna grow a 'stache?

10:17.231 --> 10:18.752
Next time
you take a piss,

10:18.900 --> 10:19.921
take some of that piss,

10:20.068 --> 10:21.254
get it on
your fingertips,

10:21.401 --> 10:22.455
do like this, here."

10:22.603 --> 10:23.923
Eww! You do it?

10:24.072 --> 10:26.091
You damn right I did it.

10:26.239 --> 10:27.426
Shit.

10:27.574 --> 10:29.295
What's going on with you,
though, son?

10:29.443 --> 10:32.830
Ain't nothing.
School about to start.

10:32.979 --> 10:34.666
So what about Bodie
and his boys?

10:34.815 --> 10:36.501
They treatin' you right?

10:36.649 --> 10:38.102
Yeah, he cool.

10:38.250 --> 10:40.638
Boy, don't lie
to your father.

10:40.785 --> 10:43.840
He don't even show up for work
half the damn time.

10:43.989 --> 10:46.743
- Bodie told me.
- I missed a few days. That's all, Dad.

10:46.891 --> 10:47.778
And what money
you do make,

10:47.926 --> 10:49.378
you waste on nonsense.

10:49.527 --> 10:51.448
And if you think
I'm gonna give you a dime

10:51.595 --> 10:54.650
for your school clothes,
you better think again.

10:54.798 --> 10:56.352
What Bodie
got you doin'?

10:56.500 --> 10:57.653
I'm a runner,
most days.

10:57.801 --> 10:59.455
Everybody got
to start somewhere.

10:59.602 --> 11:01.589
You better listen
to your father.

11:01.737 --> 11:04.426
He ain't tell you 'bout
that hair, though, huh?

11:04.574 --> 11:06.661
Yeah, he said
I gotta get it cut.

11:06.808 --> 11:07.895
I like it this way.

11:08.044 --> 11:09.129
Even the white police
lookin' out from

11:09.277 --> 11:10.864
three blocks away gonna
be able to spot you

11:11.012 --> 11:12.833
from every other nigga
out there.

11:12.981 --> 11:14.834
They gonna hop out and say,
"Look at the boy over there

11:14.983 --> 11:17.637
with the pretty-ass
ponytail. Get him."

11:17.786 --> 11:19.639
You think
I'm bullshitting.

11:19.787 --> 11:22.741
Either you real out there,
or you ain't, Nay.

11:22.890 --> 11:25.050
You see what I'm sayin'?

11:31.563 --> 11:32.917
Let me get some!

11:33.066 --> 11:34.385
Hey, yo! Over here!

11:34.533 --> 11:36.364
- Whoa! $100!
- Thanks, mister!

11:37.736 --> 11:40.068
- Thank you, Mr. Marlo!
- Thank you!

11:46.577 --> 11:48.738
That's my money, yo!

11:54.584 --> 11:57.576
Your name gonna
ring out, man.

12:00.189 --> 12:02.180
Manuel...

12:12.533 --> 12:14.053
Boy, you talk that shit
better'n me

12:14.202 --> 12:16.455
and I been dealin' with
these Mexicans for years now.

12:16.604 --> 12:17.723
Yeah, I don't think
they would call

12:17.871 --> 12:19.558
what I'm speakin'
Spanish, man.

12:19.706 --> 12:21.560
Just a dirty word
or two here or there.

12:21.708 --> 12:23.729
Yeah, well. Once you can
talk to these cats,

12:23.876 --> 12:26.231
the only thing you need
then is a truck, man.

12:26.380 --> 12:27.499
Could be runnin'
your own crew,

12:27.647 --> 12:29.501
pickin' up fresh clients.

12:29.648 --> 12:31.069
I mean,
if we put in together

12:31.216 --> 12:32.637
we could be coverin'
twice the ground,

12:32.784 --> 12:34.338
makin' twice as much.

12:34.486 --> 12:37.908
Nah, man, I got
other obligations.

12:38.056 --> 12:39.176
Oh, right.

12:39.324 --> 12:41.878
You set to be
the new Angelo Dundee.

12:42.026 --> 12:43.585
I near forgot.

12:51.568 --> 12:52.755
I thought
you already went up

12:52.902 --> 12:54.923
to Mondawmin to get
your school shit, man.

12:55.071 --> 12:56.590
Yeah,
but not all of it.

12:56.739 --> 12:57.758
And my boy,

12:57.907 --> 12:58.926
he need to pay
for his own shit

12:59.074 --> 13:00.228
and his little brother, too.

13:00.375 --> 13:01.262
The fuck this look like,

13:01.410 --> 13:03.197
a Social Services office?

13:03.345 --> 13:04.832
You want a check,
go the fuck up Rosemont.

13:04.980 --> 13:06.412
Come on, man,
I'll work for it.

13:07.848 --> 13:10.370
Nay, I took you on outta respect
for your father,

13:10.518 --> 13:12.038
a'ight, but I can't go hirin'

13:12.186 --> 13:14.173
the whole damn neighborhood.

13:14.321 --> 13:15.208
You can have
my job until

13:15.355 --> 13:17.042
you get enough
for you an' Bug.

13:17.190 --> 13:20.446
- Thanks, man.
- Yeah, work for y'all, work for me, yo.

13:20.594 --> 13:22.823
Po-po.
Step the fuck off.

13:32.538 --> 13:34.124
Looking for your man Lex.

13:34.272 --> 13:36.326
I see his broom,
but I don't see him.

13:36.474 --> 13:37.961
Where's your
number two been at?

13:38.109 --> 13:40.797
- I ain't seen him.
- Since when?

13:40.944 --> 13:43.265
I thought we were
on better terms.

13:43.413 --> 13:44.400
Or do you want me
rolling past

13:44.548 --> 13:46.569
Iookin' for Lex
every 15 minutes?

13:46.716 --> 13:48.581
He come past,
I'll call you.

13:49.685 --> 13:50.777
I will!

14:05.666 --> 14:07.999
If he come past.

14:09.169 --> 14:11.023
Oh no, I don't know.

14:11.171 --> 14:12.859
They're spinning
their wheels.

14:13.006 --> 14:14.559
You know,
poor Tony Gray,

14:14.707 --> 14:17.362
pulling 20%
of the black vote.

14:17.511 --> 14:19.864
It's embarrassing.

14:20.013 --> 14:21.032
Well, who knows
what the fuck

14:21.180 --> 14:22.367
Carcetti's
trying to prove?

14:22.514 --> 14:24.135
But I tell you,
at the end of this thing,

14:24.284 --> 14:26.871
he's gonna regret getting
on the wrong side of me.

14:27.019 --> 14:28.204
Mm-hmm.

14:28.353 --> 14:31.875
A'ight, now.
I got what you need, boy,

14:32.024 --> 14:34.377
clean tees,
any sizes, huh?

14:34.525 --> 14:36.179
Lookin' for socks, briefs,

14:36.326 --> 14:38.981
you lookin' for dice,
Zippos, cards--

14:39.130 --> 14:41.050
come on over
to the Rollin' Emporium.

14:41.197 --> 14:42.384
You ain't gotta
walk to Rite-Aid.

14:42.533 --> 14:44.219
Shit, Rite-Aid
comin' to y'all.

14:44.367 --> 14:45.586
What can I get you, baby?

14:45.735 --> 14:47.389
Fresh dice
an' a pack of Trojans.

14:47.536 --> 14:49.724
- All righty.
- You got Philly Blunts, too?

14:49.873 --> 14:50.892
Bubbles got it all, dawg.

14:51.040 --> 14:52.860
I'm the one-stop shop.

14:53.007 --> 14:55.396
- How much is that?
- Six an' a bit.

14:55.543 --> 14:57.397
Thank you.
Thank you kindly.

14:57.545 --> 14:59.166
Yes, sir, I see
what you're lookin' at.

14:59.314 --> 15:00.800
Two a deck,
name brand.

15:00.948 --> 15:01.835
You can't beat that price.

15:01.983 --> 15:04.104
Yeah, let me get
two decks, man,

15:04.252 --> 15:06.372
and a white tee,
double-X.

15:06.520 --> 15:07.940
And give me the rest
of them paint cans, too, man.

15:08.088 --> 15:11.010
All right, all right,
there you go. That's it?

15:11.158 --> 15:13.178
Yeah, what's that?

15:13.327 --> 15:15.658
How much the man owe,
Sherrod?

15:22.834 --> 15:24.354
- 13.
- Whoa whoa whoa.

15:24.503 --> 15:26.023
He asked for all the cans.

15:26.171 --> 15:28.298
Three cans is $12,
plus the other stuff.

15:29.841 --> 15:31.027
It's $19.
$19, sir.

15:31.175 --> 15:32.195
Come on, you still gettin'
off with a deal,

15:32.343 --> 15:33.863
Now, you didn't have
to move your feet.

15:34.011 --> 15:35.031
We came to you, right?

15:35.179 --> 15:38.342
My bad.
$19, like he said.

15:39.515 --> 15:40.535
Thank you very much.

15:40.683 --> 15:42.938
He's an intern,
I'm working with him.

15:43.086 --> 15:46.374
But, ma'am,
what I'm asking is

15:46.522 --> 15:49.710
when was the last time
you saw Lex?

15:49.858 --> 15:52.713
Oh, excuse me-- Curtis?

15:52.861 --> 15:54.294
Hmm?

15:55.864 --> 15:58.551
- Two days ago?
- I don't know where he at.

15:58.699 --> 16:00.257
Three days?

16:01.702 --> 16:03.156
You mind
if I look around?

16:03.303 --> 16:05.158
I'd rather you
leave my house be.

16:05.305 --> 16:08.138
Well, Ms. Anderson...

16:11.978 --> 16:13.264
your son is in trouble,

16:13.413 --> 16:15.666
and I can tell
you're upset.

16:15.814 --> 16:17.335
But the best thing
that you can do for him--

16:17.483 --> 16:19.170
the best thing that
he can do for himself--

16:19.318 --> 16:22.006
is talk to me.

16:22.153 --> 16:24.341
I'm gonna
tell you the truth:

16:24.489 --> 16:26.176
We know
he's selling drugs.

16:26.323 --> 16:27.611
And I'm gonna tell you...

16:27.758 --> 16:29.179
I don't know
nothin' about that.

16:29.326 --> 16:31.847
But I'm telling you
that I don't care

16:31.995 --> 16:33.849
he's selling drugs.

16:33.997 --> 16:36.830
I'm not even gonna
bother with that.

16:40.803 --> 16:43.591
I'm here
because of a homicide,

16:43.739 --> 16:45.460
and the way
it looks right now

16:45.608 --> 16:47.194
your boy is running
from the police

16:47.343 --> 16:49.463
behind that killing.

16:49.611 --> 16:51.164
I don't know
where he at...

16:51.312 --> 16:53.302
Ma'am...

17:07.492 --> 17:10.814
Councilman,
my people got only

17:10.963 --> 17:14.295
cost-of-living bumps
for four years.

17:15.300 --> 17:17.488
Morale is at rock bottom.

17:17.635 --> 17:19.823
All things being equal,
you'd be our guy.

17:19.971 --> 17:21.324
We like what we hear.

17:21.472 --> 17:24.160
The polls say
it's going to be Royce.

17:24.308 --> 17:25.994
We endorse you now,
we're out in the cold.

17:26.143 --> 17:28.664
Bobby... this might be
the chance to get in on

17:28.812 --> 17:30.666
the ground floor
of something better.

17:30.814 --> 17:33.168
That may be true, Major.
But for now,

17:33.316 --> 17:35.836
we're gonna play the cards
that we were dealt.

17:35.985 --> 17:38.173
Councilman,
if you were me, I'm sure--

17:38.320 --> 17:39.840
I'd cover my ass
and endorse Royce,

17:39.988 --> 17:42.175
along with the teachers
and the firefighters.

17:42.324 --> 17:43.344
But I'd also
tell my membership

17:43.492 --> 17:44.845
not to get carried away.
I mean,

17:44.993 --> 17:46.514
