What is your name,
Officer?

32:13.892 --> 32:15.883
Detective Sydnor, sir.

32:18.597 --> 32:20.984
"Major Crimes"?

32:21.131 --> 32:23.986
Shit...

32:24.134 --> 32:25.897
Enjoy your day, sir.

32:27.571 --> 32:30.233
Son, we're gonna see
about this.

32:39.881 --> 32:41.872
That's it.

32:44.353 --> 32:45.911
Yankin' that bitch.

32:48.155 --> 32:50.817
Son, that's too much knuckle.

33:00.600 --> 33:02.220
Why the fuck
you keep callin' me?

33:02.368 --> 33:03.388
But what I say, though?

33:03.535 --> 33:05.056
He got
the message, fool.

33:05.204 --> 33:06.390
Yo, Monk.
Who that, man?

33:06.538 --> 33:09.060
Andre.
Old Face Andre.

33:09.208 --> 33:11.729
Here, let me
holla at that dude.

33:11.876 --> 33:13.230
Yo, check this out, man.

33:13.379 --> 33:14.898
I'm gonna show you
how you do this

33:15.046 --> 33:16.566
right here, man.

33:16.714 --> 33:18.567
Don't rush me on shit.

33:18.716 --> 33:21.377
I'll get at you
when I'm at you.

33:25.889 --> 33:27.909
Yo, remember who
you're talking to

33:28.058 --> 33:30.218
before you say
another fuckin' word.

33:37.565 --> 33:38.919
Andre, man.

33:39.067 --> 33:40.087
Nigga need
more maintenance

33:40.235 --> 33:41.998
than both
my babies' mamas.

33:45.573 --> 33:48.700
By accident.
It was accidental.

33:51.078 --> 33:53.231
And the mayor
doesn't say anything?

33:53.380 --> 33:55.367
I think
he's pretty mad.

33:55.516 --> 33:57.769
I mean, Major,
I only took this detail

33:57.917 --> 33:59.771
to try and make sergeant
on this list.

33:59.918 --> 34:02.840
Kid, you made
sergeant already.

34:02.989 --> 34:05.342
Shit, if Royce
gets reelected,

34:05.490 --> 34:08.721
you'll be a lieutenant in two years
and a major in four.

34:10.860 --> 34:13.216
You go back down
to the hall.

34:13.364 --> 34:15.385
You act like
it never happened.

34:15.533 --> 34:17.053
You shut up.

34:17.201 --> 34:19.054
Say nothing to no one.

34:19.202 --> 34:20.389
But the mayor,
he's gonna--

34:20.538 --> 34:24.059
He's gonna watch
and see how you carry it.

34:24.206 --> 34:26.726
And kid,
you're a fucking rock.

34:26.876 --> 34:29.563
When the mayor
looks in your face,

34:29.712 --> 34:33.366
he knows he can
trust you with this.

34:33.514 --> 34:36.335
And I'll bet
in a couple of weeks,

34:36.485 --> 34:38.737
he comes asking,
real friendly-like,

34:38.886 --> 34:40.706
what are you looking
to do with the department?

34:40.855 --> 34:42.708
With your career?

34:42.857 --> 34:45.110
He's interested in you.

34:45.259 --> 34:47.313
But he doesn't mention
no blowjob,

34:47.460 --> 34:48.781
and neither do you.

34:48.929 --> 34:50.649
Uh-uh, it just lays there

34:50.797 --> 34:53.552
Iike a bad pierogi
on the plate,

34:53.699 --> 34:57.555
both of you pretending
it ain't there.

34:57.703 --> 34:59.457
What if he
screws me over?

34:59.604 --> 35:01.525
Bounces me
to a midnight shift?

35:01.674 --> 35:04.801
He does that,
you will talk.

35:11.682 --> 35:15.538
What I wouldn't give to be
in your shoes right now.

35:15.685 --> 35:17.707
Kid, careers have
been launched

35:17.854 --> 35:20.041
on a hell
of a lot less.

35:20.190 --> 35:24.182
Just shut up
and play dumb.

35:26.027 --> 35:29.717
I can do that.
No problem.

35:29.865 --> 35:31.385
Thanks, Major.

35:31.532 --> 35:34.053
Thanks for taking the time
to meet me on this.

35:34.202 --> 35:37.056
I mean, it's a weight off
my mind talking to you.

35:37.204 --> 35:38.391
It really is.

35:38.539 --> 35:40.393
Don't mention it.

35:40.541 --> 35:42.562
Maybe you get a chance
to do me a turn

35:42.709 --> 35:45.542
one day after
you make rank, huh?

35:48.548 --> 35:50.539
Oh, boy.

35:54.386 --> 35:56.377
It's all good, Carv.

36:01.059 --> 36:02.579
Because if some
federal motherfucker comes

36:02.727 --> 36:04.281
through the door,
I say, "Hey,

36:04.429 --> 36:06.016
it's all in the game."

36:06.163 --> 36:07.717
But a City Police?

36:07.864 --> 36:10.186
Baltimore City?
Hell, no.

36:10.333 --> 36:11.854
Can't be happenin',
'cause I know

36:12.002 --> 36:14.123
I have raised too much
goddamn money

36:14.271 --> 36:15.857
for the mayor
and his ticket.

36:16.006 --> 36:17.025
Hell, no!

36:17.174 --> 36:18.360
Ain't no soul
in the world

36:18.507 --> 36:20.338
that fuckin' ungrateful!

36:21.844 --> 36:24.265
- Calm down, Clay, hmm?
- Money laundering?

36:24.412 --> 36:25.867
They gonna
come talk to me

36:26.014 --> 36:27.200
about money laundering?

36:27.349 --> 36:28.703
In West Baltimore?

36:28.850 --> 36:31.038
Shit... Where do y'all
think I'm gonna

36:31.185 --> 36:33.373
raise cash for
the whole damn ticket?

36:33.521 --> 36:35.475
From laundromats
and shit?

36:35.622 --> 36:39.044
From some tiny-ass
Korean groceries?

36:39.193 --> 36:41.046
You think I have time
to ask a man

36:41.195 --> 36:43.048
why he givin' me money?

36:43.197 --> 36:44.883
Or where he gets
his money from?

36:45.032 --> 36:47.519
I'll take any motherfucker's money
if he givin' it away.

36:47.667 --> 36:49.988
- I don't wanna know.
- I know you don't wanna know.

36:50.135 --> 36:51.423
But I'm scratchin'
an' clawin'

36:51.570 --> 36:53.357
to get it done for you,
Clarence.

36:53.506 --> 36:55.926
For you and me
and the rest of the team.

36:56.073 --> 36:57.328
And who comes
through my door

36:57.476 --> 36:59.063
but a Baltimore City Police

36:59.210 --> 37:00.863
Iookin' to get up
into my shit about it.

37:01.012 --> 37:02.165
Clay, we didn't know
about that.

37:02.313 --> 37:03.900
I'm sorry, I gots
to leave up out of here

37:04.048 --> 37:05.868
before I lose
my damn mind.

37:06.016 --> 37:07.303
Nobody knew about that.

37:07.451 --> 37:08.538
You want
to run a campaign

37:08.685 --> 37:10.372
with my money
pillowed under your ass,

37:10.520 --> 37:14.148
you need your people
to back the fuck up, Clarence.

37:19.161 --> 37:20.514
Krawczyk's on line one.

37:20.662 --> 37:23.616
I'll jump on Burrell
and Demper both.

37:23.765 --> 37:24.919
Find out
what the hell's going on.

37:25.066 --> 37:27.554
Wait-- wait a minute.

37:27.702 --> 37:30.789
That new driver,
the bald-headed, white kid.

37:30.938 --> 37:32.958
Where did he
come here from?

37:33.107 --> 37:34.694
Hoskins brought
him in, I think.

37:34.841 --> 37:37.596
Hoskins?
He doesn't have a better rabbi

37:37.744 --> 37:38.996
in the department than that?

37:39.145 --> 37:41.033
Why, you want
to lose him?

37:41.180 --> 37:42.978
Let me think about it.

37:55.994 --> 37:58.615
Yeah, man, Officer Walker
be shady like that.

37:58.762 --> 38:00.450
Police be stealin', yo.

38:00.597 --> 38:03.252
Yo, what I really wanna
get is a bubble Caprice.

38:03.400 --> 38:05.087
I seen
a nice one, too.

38:05.235 --> 38:08.590
'94 caprice on 22's.
Shit was tight.

38:08.739 --> 38:10.892
You better be careful.
They almost caught you today.

38:11.040 --> 38:12.494
Nigga, they ain't
almost caught shit.

38:12.642 --> 38:14.129
Shh. Be quiet, y'all.

38:14.276 --> 38:15.496
Y'all know
who I am, right?

38:15.645 --> 38:17.931
Carver.
You a narcos.

38:18.079 --> 38:21.201
Today I'm auto theft.

38:21.349 --> 38:23.237
Fair warning.

38:23.385 --> 38:24.605
If I see any of
y'all little hoppers

38:24.752 --> 38:27.106
even smile
at a motor vehicle again,

38:27.255 --> 38:30.343
it ain't gonna be no juvenile hearing.
No, it's gonna be my people

38:30.491 --> 38:32.611
settlin' up with y'all in the alleys.
You understand?

38:32.760 --> 38:35.013
- You can't do that, yo.
- Try me, Namond.

38:35.162 --> 38:37.182
Yeah, that's right.
I know your name,

38:37.330 --> 38:38.917
I know where you live

38:39.065 --> 38:41.056
and I know where
y'all hang.

38:56.013 --> 39:00.176
Damn, yo!
Nice ride.

39:01.918 --> 39:04.306
- Hey, Bunk.
- Hmm?

39:04.453 --> 39:06.240
You have any luck
finding your shooter?

39:06.389 --> 39:08.477
Naw. He's runnin'.

39:08.624 --> 39:10.978
But at least I know who
my shooter is, right?

39:11.126 --> 39:12.647
I just got
to find the boy.

39:12.794 --> 39:14.816
- Family won't go for nothin'?
- Nah.

39:14.963 --> 39:17.117
Mother wouldn't say shit.

39:17.265 --> 39:18.819
But it wasn't the usual way
a mama lies.

39:18.967 --> 39:21.721
- What do you mean?
- I don't know.

39:21.869 --> 39:23.489
It was a weird vibe, man.

39:23.638 --> 39:24.824
I can't explain it.

39:24.972 --> 39:27.770
It was like she was off
somewhere else in her head.

39:29.643 --> 39:32.198
Line four.
Communication.

39:32.345 --> 39:34.767
- Who's up?
- I'm up. I'll take it.

39:34.914 --> 39:36.367
No, wait.

39:36.515 --> 39:38.503
If it's yours,
you lucky bitch,

39:38.651 --> 39:41.505
then it's a domestic
in a house with four wits.

39:41.653 --> 39:43.507
- You want the call?
- But I pick up that phone,

39:43.655 --> 39:45.108
do I make it unlucky?

39:45.256 --> 39:46.410
Or is it still your call?

39:46.558 --> 39:49.179
You want the call,
pick it up.

39:49.326 --> 39:51.817
If you don't, don't.

39:53.764 --> 39:55.518
Homicide. Norris.

39:55.666 --> 39:59.499
Right. Uh-huh. I got it.

40:02.171 --> 40:05.527
1400 Lanvale, in the street,
found by the post officer,

40:05.674 --> 40:07.642
no suspects,
no witnesses.

40:11.513 --> 40:13.674
Ah, man.

40:16.350 --> 40:18.910
Better to be lucky
than to be good.

40:21.821 --> 40:25.210
You wanna work
the heavy bag?

40:25.358 --> 40:27.519
G'head. Four rounds.

40:41.840 --> 40:42.726
Hey.

40:42.874 --> 40:44.227
- Hey.
- I'm Gail.

40:44.375 --> 40:46.129
I made this for you
and the other men

40:46.277 --> 40:48.798
to let you know
you're appreciated.

40:48.945 --> 40:51.734
- That's real nice.
- Peach cobbler.

40:51.883 --> 40:53.903
I'm sorry, I forgot
whose mother you are.

40:54.051 --> 40:55.137
Oh, I don't have
any boys.

40:55.285 --> 40:56.938
I just appreciate
what you been doing,

40:57.087 --> 40:59.174
you and the other coaches
volunteering and all.

40:59.321 --> 41:01.109
Well, thank you,
that's real nice.

41:01.257 --> 41:03.978
I got three girls. Y'all don't
teach girls, though, do you?

41:04.126 --> 41:07.848
- No, I'm real old-fashioned about that.
- Oh, I agree wit' you.

41:07.997 --> 41:10.517
Men should be men
and women should be women.

41:10.665 --> 41:12.496
That's what I think.

41:18.005 --> 41:20.526
Single wound,
upper back, no casings,

41:20.674 --> 41:22.194
no witnesses, and nothing
on the canvas.

41:22.341 --> 41:24.863
- Dead when you got here?
- Actually not.

41:25.011 --> 41:27.365
He was still conscious
and coughin' blood when I pulled up.

41:27.513 --> 41:29.600
- You ask who shot him?
- Yeah, I asked who shot him.

41:29.749 --> 41:32.149
He said it was
a guy with a gun.

41:38.422 --> 41:41.377
Yo, why the fuck
you keep calling me?

41:41.525 --> 41:43.079
He got the message, fool.

41:43.227 --> 41:44.347
Yo, Monk,
who that, man?

41:44.494 --> 41:46.827
Andre.
Old Face Andre.

41:48.532 --> 41:49.885
Yo, Monk,
who that, man?

41:50.033 --> 41:52.688
Andre.
Old Face Andre.

41:52.835 --> 41:55.657
Lemme key that.

41:55.804 --> 41:57.058
Yo, Monk.
Who that, man?

41:57.207 --> 41:59.367
Andre.
Old Face Andre.

42:02.978 --> 42:05.208
Yo, check this out, man.

42:07.315 --> 42:09.336
Don't rush me on shit.

42:09.484 --> 42:11.816
- I'll get at you when I'm at you.
- I'm just saying...

42:14.589 --> 42:16.175
Old Face Andre.

42:16.323 --> 42:17.676
Tryin' to reup
with Monk Metcalf.

42:17.824 --> 42:20.012
Yeah, well, Monk took the call
on his cell phone.

42:20.160 --> 42:21.680
But that second voice
ranked him.

42:21.827 --> 42:23.148
Ranked everybody,
by the sound of it.

42:23.295 --> 42:25.683
Marlo Stanfield.
On the phone.

42:25.831 --> 42:28.753
The way he shut that call down,
I'd say, yeah, that was him.

42:28.900 --> 42:30.954
Yeah, but what was all that
in the background? Fireworks, or--

42:31.103 --> 42:33.991
Naw, it was regular intervals.
Semi-auto from the sound.

42:34.139 --> 42:35.692
Target practice, maybe.

42:35.840 --> 42:38.027
Either that
or a firing squad.

42:38.176 --> 42:41.797
There are no bodies
on this guy in months,

42:41.945 --> 42:43.199
but we get him
on the phone

42:43.347 --> 42:44.867
and it sounds
like a war zone.

42:45.014 --> 42:47.203
Well, at least he gets
on a phone now and then.

42:47.351 --> 42:50.038
- That's something.
- Sounds arrogant, doesn't he?

42:50.186 --> 42:52.374
Like he's the lil' king
of everything.

42:52.522 --> 42:54.352
Ah. Youth.

43:09.637 --> 43:10.968
Yo, bubs.

43:13.974 --> 43:16.828
Thought you asleep.

43:16.976 --> 43:19.665
If you want...

43:19.812 --> 43:22.145
I could go
to school some.

43:23.982 --> 43:25.836
I ain't been
for a while,

43:25.984 --> 43:29.673
so I don't even
know if I can.

43:29.822 --> 43:32.642
But if you
want me to go...

43:32.790 --> 43:34.781
ain't no thing.

44:22.535 --> 44:24.655
His Honor was mad?

44:24.803 --> 44:26.889
I can't begin
to describe it.

44:27.038 --> 44:29.759
- What's he want from us?
- To block the subpoenas,

44:29.908 --> 44:32.495
but he knows we can't
once those things go out.

44:32.643 --> 44:34.831
What I could promise him

44:34.979 --> 44:38.100
is no more surprises
out of our shop.

44:38.249 --> 44:40.202
Is this that
cocksucker McNulty?

44:40.351 --> 44:43.839
Not this time. He's been gone
from that unit a year.

44:43.987 --> 44:47.342
My best guess would be
Lester Freamon.

44:47.489 --> 44:49.877
- Freamon?
- Lester's got a helluva game.

44:50.025 --> 44:51.778
Well, we need to sit
on the motherfucker.

44:51.927 --> 44:52.847
All that unit needs,
Commissioner,

44:52.994 --> 44:55.122
is proper supervision.

44:57.798 --> 44:58.985
Hey, the State of Maryland

44:59.133 --> 45:00.754
just lost another
cooperating witness,

45:00.901 --> 45:03.156
and I just found a lot
of fucking overtime.

45:03.303 --> 45:05.458
This case went from
a who-gives-a-fuck drug murder

45:05.605 --> 45:07.596
to straight-up red ball.

45:11.611 --> 45:14.602
Fuck, I should've
picked up that phone.

45:17.950 --> 45:19.137
Hey, Sarge.
My boy's a witness.

45:19.284 --> 45:21.071
Drug case pending
in part 18.

45:21.220 --> 45:23.306
You know for sure
he's killed for that reason?

45:23.454 --> 45:25.408
Don't know shit. But from the look
of the court computer,

45:25.556 --> 45:27.344
this guy's
the state's whole case.

45:27.491 --> 45:29.979
Don't put it in the 24 that
the guy was a witness.

45:30.128 --> 45:32.148
Trust me,
we do not wanna kick shit

45:32.296 --> 45:34.817
in an election year.
Work the case, take the O.T.,

45:34.964 --> 45:38.298
but bury the witness angle
till we know for sure.

45:39.969 --> 45:41.960
And close the door.

45:56.817 --> 45:58.171
Yeah.

45:58.319 --> 45:59.839
It's Landsman. Homicide.

45:59.986 --> 46:02.408
Is the major
in this morning?

46:02.555 --> 46:04.209
Next order of business:
class rules.

46:04.357 --> 46:06.244
It helps if the team
is constant on these.

46:06.392 --> 46:08.280
Less wiggle room
for the children.

46:08.428 --> 46:09.447
Mrs. Scott?

46:09.594 --> 46:11.483
Same as last year,
double space.

46:11.630 --> 46:13.318
Language Arts,
we grade a lot of papers.

46:13.465 --> 46:14.952
It doesn't make them
write any better,

46:15.100 --> 46:16.886
but it saves my eyesight.

46:17.035 --> 46:19.223
Make sure you
demonstrate it for them.

46:19.370 --> 46:21.457
Some of them think double-space
means more space between words.

46:21.605 --> 46:23.126
I'd of thought
by eighth grade--

46:23.274 --> 46:26.162
Rule of thumb around here,
Mr. Pryzbylewski: Never assume.

46:26.310 --> 46:27.629
Explain what
you want them to do,

46:27.778 --> 46:29.765
have them do it,
then explain again.

46:29.914 --> 46:32.134
With time and patience,
they'll get it.

46:32.282 --> 46:35.103
- Mrs. Shapiro?
- It's easier to keep track of lab work

46:35.251 --> 46:37.072
if we all use
the same heading.

46:37.219 --> 46:39.941
Upper right-hand corner,
above the first blue line:

46:40.089 --> 46:43.476
name, date, and class number,
in that order?

46:43.625 --> 46:45.946
Mr. Pryzbylewski, do you have
anything you want addressed?

46:46.094 --> 46:48.582
Can we have them
not chew gum?

46:48.730 --> 46:50.650
They won't do it
in Ms. Sampson's class,

46:50.798 --> 46:53.118
but in four years, I have not
been able to stop them.

46:53.267 --> 46:55.955
You can try, but first year,
it's best to stick with basics.

46:56.103 --> 46:57.356
And team rules--
we can only go

46:57.504 --> 46:59.391
with what
we can all enforce.

46:59.539 --> 47:01.993
Also, keep your
windows closed.

47:02.142 --> 47:04.762
Makes them drowsy,
and drowsy's good.

47:04.910 --> 47:07.232
There's a lot to learn.
But for now,

47:07.380 --> 47:09.434
build in lots of activities
in your lesson plan.

47:09.581 --> 47:10.601
You can't have enough.

47:10.750 --> 47:13.582
You keep them busy,
you keep them off-guard.

47:16.955 --> 47:19.910
You need soft eyes.

47:20.057 --> 47:22.048
Excuse me?

47:24.961 --> 47:26.282
Yeah, but that
doesn't prevent you

47:26.430 --> 47:28.483
from giving more
under your wife's name,

47:28.631 --> 47:30.218
your children, if they
got separate accounts...

47:30.366 --> 47:31.993
yeah.

47:33.435 --> 47:36.090
Sorry, Richie,
can you hold a moment?

47:36.239 --> 47:37.958
Your buddy
from the F.O.P.

47:38.106 --> 47:39.294
And he says
it's important.

47:39.441 --> 47:41.395
Hey, Stan.

47:41.543 --> 47:44.130
I'm a little busy
losing an election here.

47:44.279 --> 47:46.232
You remember about
six months ago,

47:46.380 --> 47:47.800
you told me
to keep an eye for

47:47.948 --> 47:49.569
any witnesses
gettin' clipped?

47:49.717 --> 47:51.708
You remember that?

47:53.286 --> 47:55.777
Who's better than me,
Tommy?

47:57.791 --> 48:00.145
Hey, Richie,
can I call you back?

48:00.292 --> 48:02.021
Thanks.

48:07.066 --> 48:09.086
Anything else you want me
to do, Miss Donnelly?

48:09.233 --> 48:10.587
Uh...

48:10.736 --> 48:12.722
you live near
Duquan Weems, correct?

48:12.870 --> 48:14.591
Dukie?

48:14.739 --> 48:16.792
I want you to take
this to his house.

48:16.941 --> 48:18.295
These clothes won't
stay clean long.

48:18.442 --> 48:20.629
Make sure you deliver
them just to Duquan,

48:20.778 --> 48:22.097
not any of the adults
in the house.

48:22.245 --> 48:24.265
- Just Duquan.
- Want me to do it tonight?

48:24.414 --> 48:26.936
that would be great.
And, Crystal, thanks for today.

48:27.083 --> 48:29.437
You're welcome,
Miss Donnelly.

48:29.585 --> 48:31.606
- Can I help you?
- Yes, ma'am.

48:31.754 --> 48:33.274
This young man has to be
registered for school.

48:33.422 --> 48:36.110
- Does he attend here?
- He should.

48:36.257 --> 48:39.124
What I mean is, what grade
were you in last year, dear?

48:41.062 --> 48:43.115
He kinda lost his way
some time ago.

48:43.264 --> 48:44.517
He's livin'
with me now.

48:44.666 --> 48:45.618
And you are his...

48:45.766 --> 48:47.757
Uncle.
I'm his uncle.

48:49.103 --> 48:51.264
Come into my office.

48:57.777 --> 48:59.767
Thank you.
Excuse me.

49:16.926 --> 49:19.190
Yo, look at coach
workin' it, yo.

49:23.233 --> 49:25.486
A'ight, man, break.
That's what I like to see, baby.

49:25.635 --> 49:27.589
That's what I like to see.
You gotta use that left

49:27.736 --> 49:31.092
- a little more, though, a'ight?
- Yo, man, you finished?

49:31.240 --> 49:33.426
- Got another two minutes.
- Fuck that, I got a fight coming up.

49:33.575 --> 49:34.762
You can come back
later, a'ight?

49:34.909 --> 49:36.162
Yo, man said he got
one more round, a'ight?

49:36.310 --> 49:37.430
Step aside, youngin'.

49:37.578 --> 49:39.299
Naw, man, bag is mine
for four rounds

49:39.447 --> 49:42.468
- and I only did three.
- Fuck that.

49:42.617 --> 49:44.270
What the fuck you
tryin' to prove, huh?

49:44.417 --> 49:46.271
Whoa, whoa. Come on, man,
come on. Come on.

49:46.419 --> 49:48.440
- What's going on, boy?
- I got a fight Saturday night,

49:48.587 --> 49:49.608
an' the boy won't
get off the bag.

49:49.755 --> 49:51.176
What the fuck he on
the bag for anyway, huh?

49:51.323 --> 49:53.211
He don't even fight.
He don't even spar.

49:53.360 --> 49:54.512
Spar with
your ass any day.

49:54.661 --> 49:56.280
- Come on, then.
- Hey hey hey.

49:56.428 --> 49:57.548
Y'all be cool,
you hear me?

49:57.696 --> 49:59.617
I ain't putting up
with this foolishness.

49:59.764 --> 50:02.119
Come here, Michael.

50:02.267 --> 50:04.988
- I can work the bag now, right?
- Not yet. Just wait.

50:05.135 --> 50:07.691
- You said four rounds.
- Yeah, I know what I said.

50:07.838 --> 50:10.626
You finish up your rounds,
and then Justin gets on.

50:10.775 --> 50:12.561
I don't want hear
no more street talk.

50:12.709 --> 50:14.797
We boxin' up in here,
we ain't fightin'.

50:14.945 --> 50:16.298
He wanna get in
the ring with me,

50:16.445 --> 50:18.800
- we can go.
- Look here, look here,

50:18.949 --> 50:20.935
Iet me tell you something:
You can come here,

50:21.083 --> 50:22.469
work out,
use the equipment.

50:22.618 --> 50:23.805
But nobody
gets in that ring

50:23.952 --> 50:25.639
unless they're being trained.

50:25.787 --> 50:27.778
You wanna be trained?

50:28.957 --> 50:30.577
I've been watching you
hit that bag.

50:30.724 --> 50:32.312
You got
a natural right hand,

50:32.460 --> 50:34.647
the way you throw it,
the way you land it.

50:34.796 --> 50:35.982
Now if I was
to train you,

50:36.130 --> 50:37.417
we'd have to start
with floor work.

50:37.565 --> 50:39.318
'Cause see, if you don't
know how to move,

50:39.466 --> 50:42.120
you ain't got no business
being in that ring.

50:42.269 --> 50:43.822
So what you think?

50:43.971 --> 50:46.803
I'd train you myself,
personally.

50:49.142 --> 50:50.996
Nah, really I just wanna keep

50:51.143 --> 50:52.496
doing what I been doing.

50:52.644 --> 50:53.975
All right.

51:00.652 --> 51:01.771
Let's see that right.

51:01.919 --> 51:02.908
Uh-huh.

51:16.832 --> 51:18.586
Is Dukie here?

51:18.734 --> 51:21.355
What's that?
That's for Duquan, right?

51:21.503 --> 51:24.124
I take it to him.

51:24.273 --> 51:25.626
Gimme.

51:25.773 --> 51:27.794
Hey, Crystal.

51:27.942 --> 51:29.796
Miss Donnelly said
to give you these.

51:29.944 --> 51:31.775
Okay.
I'll be right down.

51:33.947 --> 51:36.335
What?

51:36.483 --> 51:38.604
And for either of
my opponents to suggest

51:38.752 --> 51:40.906
that downtown development
comes at the expense

51:41.054 --> 51:43.074
of our city's neighborhoods,

51:43.223 --> 51:47.444
well, that's just unfair
and, uh, divisive.

51:47.593 --> 51:50.648
For them to suggest
that my administration

51:50.795 --> 51:53.717
has not been
responsive, well...

51:53.865 --> 51:56.086
Economic development
cannot be a band-aid.

51:56.234 --> 51:59.823
It is a long-term process
that requires commitment

51:59.970 --> 52:02.825
to retraining our workforce
and, as I said before,

52:02.973 --> 52:04.259
this can only be successful

52:04.408 --> 52:05.862
in a city where
people feel safe.

52:06.010 --> 52:07.763
So before we can
even begin to think about

52:07.910 --> 52:09.297
Iuring new industries to Baltimore,

52:09.445 --> 52:10.999
we need to think about
how we can make

52:11.147 --> 52:14.335
these neighborhoods
and this city safe once again.

52:14.484 --> 52:16.938
Mr. Carcetti may think
it's in his interest

52:17.085 --> 52:18.439
to exploit people's fears.

52:18.588 --> 52:22.276
He's been doing it
throughout this campaign.

52:22.423 --> 52:23.776
I'm offended by it,
personally.

52:23.925 --> 52:25.512
But the fact is,

52:25.661 --> 52:28.982
that violent crime
is down citywide,

52:29.130 --> 52:31.850
and our police department
is working hard

52:31.999 --> 52:33.118
to keep it that way--

52:33.267 --> 52:36.121
and will continue to do so
under my administration.

52:36.269 --> 52:37.289
Councilman Carcetti,

52:37.437 --> 52:39.791
you have two minutes
to respond.

52:39.939 --> 52:41.126
Does anyone in this room
really believe

52:41.273 --> 52:42.961
that crime is down
in Baltimore?

52:43.108 --> 52:44.629
You calling me a liar,
Tommy?

52:44.777 --> 52:46.864
Gentleman, please.
No personal interactions.

52:47.011 --> 52:49.699
- Councilman Carcetti.
- Can the mayor honestly tell

52:49.847 --> 52:52.170
the people of Rosemont,
of Belair Edison,

52:52.317 --> 52:53.637
of Highlandtown
or Cherry Hill

52:53.785 --> 52:56.640
there's less drug-dealing,
less violence?

52:56.787 --> 52:58.942
Any statistics coming
from the police department

52:59.089 --> 53:00.809
cannot be trusted,
because under this mayor,

53:00.957 --> 53:02.578
the police are more concerned

53:02.726 --> 53:05.780
with protecting Clarence Royce
politically than fighting crime.

53:05.929 --> 53:08.750
There's no leadership
and morale has never been lower.

53:08.899 --> 53:10.118
I'll change that.

53:10.266 --> 53:12.419
It's business as usual
down at City Hall

53:12.568 --> 53:14.923
and as a result,
our response to crime

53:15.070 --> 53:17.257
has been characterized
time and time again

53:17.406 --> 53:19.927
by wanton indifference.

53:20.075 --> 53:21.460
...32 yards!

53:21.609 --> 53:24.764
What do I mean
by business as usual?

53:24.912 --> 53:26.999
What do I mean
by wanton indifference?

53:27.147 --> 53:29.602
Well, last night
in West Baltimore,

53:29.750 --> 53:31.437
on Lanvale Street,

53:31.584 --> 53:34.072
another citizen
was shot and killed.

53:34.221 --> 53:35.907
This time, the victim
was a key witness

53:36.055 --> 53:37.842
in a drug case that
had yet to come to court.

53:37.990 --> 53:40.844
Courageously, this man
had agreed to testify

53:40.993 --> 53:42.813
in two weeks time
in that case.

53:42.961 --> 53:44.882
The police should have
been protecting him.

53:45.030 --> 53:47.952
They were not,
and he was murdered.

53:48.099 --> 53:50.120
- Oh, shit.
- Why? Because this mayor...

53:50.267 --> 53:51.454
You're prime-time, Eddie.

53:51.603 --> 53:53.823
...would not spend the money
to protect him.

53:53.971 --> 53:55.792
Now I have no doubt
that in a moment or two

53:55.940 --> 53:57.627
Clarence Royce will
accuse me of exploiting

53:57.774 --> 53:59.962
this man's death
for my own political purpose.

54:00.110 --> 54:02.064
But the truth is,

54:02.212 --> 54:04.999
a year ago I wrote
the mayor a letter.

54:05.148 --> 54:06.601
I have copies for anyone
who wants one.

54:06.750 --> 54:08.970
I begged him
to spend the money

54:09.118 --> 54:10.871
and make witness protection
a priority.

54:11.019 --> 54:12.372
He ignored me.

54:12.521 --> 54:14.275
I even teamed up
with our legislative leaders--

54:14.422 --> 54:15.775
Delegate Watkins
and others--

54:15.924 --> 54:17.744
to get matching funds
for witness protection

54:17.892 --> 54:18.945
approved in Annapolis.

54:19.093 --> 54:21.081
And incredibly
those matching funds

54:21.229 --> 54:22.949
were never claimed
by this administration.

54:23.097 --> 54:25.417
Now to mention this
now may be exploitive--

54:25.565 --> 54:27.953
I don't know.
I only know it's true,

54:28.101 --> 54:30.256
and on such truths
I ask the voters

54:30.403 --> 54:32.872
of our city
to consider a change.

54:37.243 --> 54:38.896
Folks, please, please,
hold your applause

54:39.044 --> 54:41.765
until after the round
of questions is over.

54:41.913 --> 54:42.833
Mayor Royce?

54:42.981 --> 54:46.103
No more surprises, huh?

54:46.251 --> 54:49.872
I am unaware of the specifics
of the incident

54:50.020 --> 54:52.141
to which Councilman Carcetti
is referring,

54:52.289 --> 54:55.477
uh, so I can't answer
that directly, um...

54:55.626 --> 54:58.981
however, I can say
that this city places

54:59.128 --> 55:02.817
the highest priority
on protecting those citizens

55:02.965 --> 55:04.418
who come forward to testify,

55:04.567 --> 55:07.354
and we will continue
to do so.

55:07.502 --> 55:11.358
Mr. Carcetti states
that he wrote a letter

55:11.505 --> 55:14.395
expressing his concerns,
and I'm sure that he did.

55:14.542 --> 55:15.862
I mean it's-- it's--

55:16.011 --> 55:17.397
it's easy enough
to write letters

55:17.545 --> 55:20.033
when all you have to do
is write letters.

55:20.181 --> 55:23.402
But when you
are required

55:23.550 --> 55:25.904
to run a city

55:26.052 --> 55:28.907
on limited resources,

55:29.054 --> 55:31.076
and balance priorities,

55:31.223 --> 55:33.912
well, then-- well,
then you understand

55:34.059 --> 55:36.913
that writing letters will
not solve the problem.

55:37.062 --> 55:38.689
Oh, no...

55:40.231 --> 55:42.419
Shit, girl.

55:42.567 --> 55:45.588
You know
I'm-a roll wit' you.

55:45.735 --> 55:49.759
Huh, I need
some kinda break.

55:49.906 --> 55:52.067
Mm-hmm.

56:06.622 --> 56:09.021
Oh, shit.

56:21.801 --> 56:23.555
Ain't nothin' worse
than them bitches

56:23.703 --> 56:27.726
with fucked-up nails
at the blackjack table.

56:27.873 --> 56:30.694
You know.

56:30.842 --> 56:33.164
Hold on.

56:33.311 --> 56:34.898
You think my son
gonna go up

56:35.046 --> 56:37.378
to that school lookin'
like himself?

56:42.887 --> 56:44.741
And I don't believe
we can get a handle on crime

56:44.889 --> 56:46.908
until we get a handle
on the schools.

56:47.057 --> 56:49.077
Because we need to be
thinking about these kids

56:49.225 --> 56:51.246
before the corners
take them.

56:51.394 --> 56:53.725
And this means a renewed focus
on our schools...

